newsitem.title: UK: NWE gasoline barges steady to firmer, cargoes flat.
newsitem.headline: NWE gasoline barges steady to firmer, cargoes flat.

text.p: NWE gasoline barges were steady to firmer on Thursday but activity was thin, traders said.
Eurograde barges changed hands at $207.50 fob ARA and prices were quoted at similar levels for most of the day.
Regular barges were not heard traded but the market was assessed some $9 below Eurograde.
A mixed Eurograde/leaded cargo was heard to have been sold out of Antwerp but the price was not known. The cargo was thought likely to be moving to the Thames.
